22/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Bulgaria's possible participation in protecting Macedonia's airspace was the main topic of the three-day visit of Bulgarian Army Chief of Staff General Nikola Kolev to Macedonia. 
Kolev and his Macedonian counterpart, General Georgi Bojadjiev, also discussed expanding bilateral military co-operation and Bulgaria's support of Macedonia's efforts to join NATO. 
Kolev left Skopje on Thursday (21 October).
In other news, Greek Foreign Minister Petros Molyviatis is due to visit Skopje on Friday. 
Talks with Macedonian leaders will reportedly focus on a possible solution of the name dispute between the two countries. 
(24 Chasa, Trud - 22/10/04; Makfax - 21/10/04)
